    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="284"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Note by the Secretaries of the Joint Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> 606</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-22">22 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Collaboration With the U. S. S. R.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The following paragraph, from a radio from General <persName corresp="#p_DJR1"
                        >Deane</persName> to General <persName corresp="#p_MGC1"
                    >Marshall</persName>, is submitted by General <persName corresp="#p_MGC1"
                        >Marshall</persName> to the Joint Chiefs of Staff for their
                    consideration:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“I suggest that the Joint Chiefs of Staff put the Russians on the defensive
                        at once by having some request to make of the Russians. I think it is
                        important that we are not put in a position of doing all the explaining. You
                        might include the following subjects: built [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]
                        bases; improved communications and interchange of weather; shuttle bomber
                        bases, and coordination of timing reference <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                        </gloss>.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Royal</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MAJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">A. J. McFarland</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Joint Secretariat</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
